    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-18T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-18T17:00:00-05:00" n="237"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">714.44A15/232: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Des Portes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-18T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 18, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Personal for the Under Secretary.<note n="2" xml:id="d237fn1">Sumner
                        Welles.</note> Upon my return here I find a strongly revived interest among
                    high Guatemalan officials regarding Belize. It is evident that they have
                    expected me to bring some definite news regarding progress in the
                    negotiations.</p>
                <p>From a statement made by the Under Secretary for Foreign Affairs it is clear that
                    President Ubico hopes to receive Belize outright in connection with the Lease
                    Lend Bill.<note n="3" xml:id="d237fn2">Approved March 11, 1941; 55 Stat.
                        31.</note>
                </p>
                <p>This matter is certain to come up for discussion at an early date notably when I
                    call on the President. I should consequently appreciate any information which
                    you may permit me to communicate to the President and other appropriate
                    Guatemalan officials if only in order that they may not indulge in unwarrantedly
                    high hopes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Des Portes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
